          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertOverpunch7ToDecimal",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a 7-character overpunch numeric string into a decimal value. Overpunch is a technique used in mainframe systems where the last character of a numeric string indicates the sign and sometimes the last digit of the number. This function interprets such strings and returns the corresponding decimal value."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
